Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper uses neural network methods, specifically a combination of CNN and RNN, to predict sea level anomalies. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence.
2. cs.LG - The paper uses machine learning techniques to develop a prediction model for sea level anomalies. This falls under the category of machine learning.
3. cs.CV - The paper uses a convolutional neural network (CNN) to analyze the spatial evolution of sea level. This falls under the category of computer vision.
4. cs.NE - The paper uses neural network methods to predict sea level anomalies. This falls under the category of neural networks.
5. cs.OH - The paper deals with the impact of anthropogenic global warming on sea level change, which falls under the category of other computer science topics.
